# Cloudflare Pages headers for the blog.
#
# knowledge.json is read CROSS-ORIGIN by the host's `// ask` assistant
# (naufal-host.pages.dev fetches it at runtime, the same way the quality
# dashboard reads health.json), so it needs permissive CORS. It's public,
# non-credentialed static JSON, so `*` is safe.
#
# Set ACAO ONCE: Cloudflare Pages merges matching rules, so a duplicate
# Access-Control-Allow-Origin becomes an invalid `*, *` that browsers reject
# (see ../../docs/gotchas.md #21).
/knowledge.json
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
